    "Background": {
      "text": "Abnormal buildup of peritoneal fluid\nMost commonly caused by portal hypertension\nAscites fluid can become infected (spontaneous bacterial peritonitis), carrying a mortality rate between 30%-90%\n[1]",
      "subsections": {
        "Causes": {
          "text": "Cirrhosis\n81%\n[2]\nMalignancy 10%\nHeart failure\n3%\nTuberculosis\n2%\nOther 4%",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
